insert into "books" ("description", "image_url", "title") values ('The success of parties'' policy agendas depends in large part on the loyal roll-call voting behavior of the rank-and-file. Yet many members have electoral incentives to behave disloyally. How do parties incentivize loyalty for such members? In this paper I explore one possibility: that the parties reward loyal members with safer districts during the redistricting process, and that members use loyalty as a means of obtaining a safer district. Using data spanning the period 1952-2012, I find evidence that loyal members get safer districts than less loyal members, but the evidence is mixed as to whether members actively seek out these rewards.', DEFAULT, 'The Loyalty Gerrymander');
